<h2>Resources in This Category</h2>
<ul>

    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.cs.uwaterloo.ca/~alopez-o/math-faq/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Frequently Asked Questions in Mathematics</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.cs.uwaterloo.ca/~alopez-o/math-faq/</strong></font> <br /> Covers diverse topics such as algebra structure, names for large numbers, how to compute pi and games.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.stonehill.edu/compsci/History_Math/math-read.htm" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>How to Read Mathematics</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.stonehill.edu/compsci/History_Math/math-read.htm</strong></font> <br /> Article categorizes some of the strategies for a mathematics reading protocol.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://mathforum.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Math Forum</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://mathforum.org/</strong></font> <br /> Features combined archive and portal to web resources, educational issues, help forums, mailing lists, and teaching materials.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Wolfram MathWorld</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://mathworld.wolfram.com/</strong></font> <br /> Formerly Eric Weisstein&#039;s World of Mathematics. Glossary of terms. Material ranges from undergraduate to research level.</p>
    </li>	
</ul>

